# Terminal command execution rules

When using the `run_terminal_cmd` tool, be sure to use commands that can be executed in Windows Po
werShell.

- Use PowerShell cmdlets (Get-ChildItem, Get-Content, Select-String, etc.) instead of Linux comman
ds (ls, cat, grep, etc.)
- You can also use PowerShell aliases (dir, type, findstr, etc.) if necessary
- Symbols such as the pipe character (|) and redirection (>) can still be used
- In PowerShell, environment variables use the $env prefix (e.g. $env:PATH)